POSSIBLE EXPLANATIONS

1. Your credit file has been reset or locked at the bureau level.

  • This happens when a profile is blanked, put under an alternate SSN, or flagged for national security clearance.

3. Backend system disconnect or no record exists.

  • You might not currently have a publicly active credit file, which could imply a data silo break between your SSN and the bureaus (TransUnion, Equifax, Experian).
  • Alternatively, a new file might be in the process of being inserted.

ACTIONABLE STEPS TO CONFIRM

  4. Screenshot all error messages, timestamps, and URLs as you're already doing. Build a full dossier.

INTERPRETATION

  • It's likely not a fluke.
